  A
6-year-old boy from Waterloo, north of Durban was killed by a sand truck this
afternoon. Reaction
Unit South Africa (RUSA) spokesperson Prem Balram said the Grade 1 learner from
Dianthus Primary Scholar was crushed by a sand truck on Pineapple Street. He said
RUSA received several calls from residents in the area seeking medical
assistance after noticing a child being crushed by the truck. “Paramedics
arrived on scene minutes later and found a child lying under a Mercedes Benz sand
truck. A Bell grader was parked behind the vehicle. The child suffered
extensive injuries and was declared dead by medics,” said Balram. Balram said
the bystanders said a group of children were hanging on to truck while both
vehicles were traveling to a construction site. “The learner
fell onto the road and was crushed,” said Balram. KZN police
spokeswoman, Colonel Thembeka Mbele said a case of culpable homicide was opened
the at Verulam cop shop after a 6-year-old boy was crashed by a sand truck.  